{"word":"δεσπόζω","slug":"δεσπόζω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>δεσπόζω</b></el> <p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a> <i>to be lord</i> or <i>master, gain the mastery</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> <i>to be lord</i> or <i>master of</i>, <b>Hhymn.</b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <el>δεσπόζειν φόβης</el> <i>to own</i> the lock of hair, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>; <a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>to master</i>, <el>δ. λόγου</el> <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <i>to lord it over</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}